Part 2: Type or handwritten answers both ok¶

Part 2-1
For a moving average process $\{X_t\}_{t\geq 0}$ of the form

$$X_t = 0.25 W_{t-2} + 0.5 W_{t-1} + W_{t},$$

determine mean function, auto-covariance function, and auto-correlation function of $X_t$. Is $\{X_t\}_{t\geq 0}$ stationary? Why or why not?

Part 2-2
Consider a time series $\{X_t\}_{t\geq 0}$ such that

$$X_t=3 -2 t + W_t.$$

(a) Find mean function, auto-covariance function, and auto-correlation function of $\{X_t\}_{t\geq 0}$. Determine if $\{X_t\}_{t\geq 0}$ is stationary or not, and explain your reasons.

(b) Let $\{Y_t\}_{t\geq 0}$ be a time series such that $Y_t:=X_t - X_{t-2}$. Find mean function, auto-covariance function, and auto-correlation function of $\{Y_t\}_{t\geq 0}$. Determine if $\{Y_t\}_{t\geq 0}$ is stationary or not, and explain your reasons.

(c) $$V_t: =\frac{1}{11} \sum_{j=-5}^{j=5} X_{t-j},$$. Find the mean function and the simplified expression of $V_t$. Is $V_t$ stationary? Why or why not?
